I have stocked my heart...

1491
01:24:13,137 --> 01:24:15,264
with icy frigidaire.

1492
01:24:15,973 --> 01:24:18,350
And I mean to care for no one...

1493
01:24:23,063 --> 01:24:25,524
because I’m through with love.

1494
01:24:28,735 --> 01:24:30,529
Why did you lead me to think...

1495
01:24:30,737 --> 01:24:33,157
you could care?

1496
01:24:33,991 --> 01:24:35,742
You didn’t need me...

1497
01:24:35,951 --> 01:24:38,537
for you had your share...

1498
01:24:39,121 --> 01:24:40,998
of friends around you...

1499
01:24:41,331 --> 01:24:43,750
to hound you and swear...

1500
01:24:44,001 --> 01:24:46,420
with deep emotion...

1501
01:24:47,254 --> 01:24:49,131
devotion to you.

1502
01:24:51,300 --> 01:24:53,760
Goodbye to spring...

1503
01:24:54,219 --> 01:24:56,513
and all it meant to me.

1504
01:24:57,097 --> 01:24:59,683
It can never bring...

1505
01:25:00,225 --> 01:25:02,811
the things that used to be.

1506
01:25:03,437 --> 01:25:05,898
For I must have you...

1507
01:25:06,857 --> 01:25:08,650
or no one.

1508
01:25:11,528 --> 01:25:13,614
And so I’m through with love.

1509
01:27:07,394 --> 01:27:11,231
I wonder what would’ve
happened if we’d stayed together.

1510
01:27:14,109 --> 01:27:16,612
That’s something
we’ll never know.

1511
01:27:17,738 --> 01:27:19,406
We’ve managed to produce...

1512
01:27:19,865 --> 01:27:21,283
a fabulous daughter.

1513
01:27:21,533 --> 01:27:23,911
She is unbelievable.

1514
01:27:24,119 --> 01:27:27,581
She’s got your looks,
fortunately...

1515
01:27:27,831 --> 01:27:29,917
and my magic personality.

1516
01:27:30,209 --> 01:27:31,877
She is wonderful.

1517
01:27:32,085 --> 01:27:35,506
And you’ve been very happy
with Bob, so that’s good.

1518
01:27:35,756 --> 01:27:36,799
He’s wonderful.

1519
01:27:37,049 --> 01:27:38,884
-You couldn’t have done better.
-No.

1520
01:27:41,303 --> 01:27:43,889
There have been a few
times, you’ll admit...

1521
01:27:44,097 --> 01:27:48,393
you did call me in an emergency
and I had to come bail you out.

1522
01:27:48,811 --> 01:27:50,270
I know.

1523
01:27:50,604 --> 01:27:53,315
Two major fights
with Bob, and...

1524
01:27:53,524 --> 01:27:57,653
one disgusting lump that turned
out to be benign...

1525
01:27:57,903 --> 01:27:59,112
though you were in a panic.

1526
01:27:59,363 --> 01:28:00,823
You were there for me.

1527
01:28:01,031 --> 01:28:02,574
And you for me.

1528
01:28:02,783 --> 01:28:03,909
And I appreciate it.

1529
01:28:04,159 --> 01:28:07,496
I think we’ve been
better friends...

1530
01:28:07,746 --> 01:28:09,164
than husband and wife.

1531
01:28:09,373 --> 01:28:11,291
Yeah, we probably have.

1532
01:28:11,708 --> 01:28:14,753
But nobody made me
laugh the way you did.

1533
01:28:14,962 --> 01:28:17,297
I love Bob with all my
heart, it isn’t that.

1534
01:28:17,506 --> 01:28:21,260
It’s just that you could always
push that button in me.

1535
01:28:21,885 --> 01:28:24,179
So why is that so important?

1536
01:28:24,513 --> 01:28:25,973
I don’t know.

1537
01:28:26,223 --> 01:28:27,683
Maybe we’re crazy.

1538
01:28:31,812 --> 01:28:35,566
That girl that dumped you
today, did she make you laugh?

1539
01:28:35,858 --> 01:28:36,984
I don’t know.

1540
01:28:37,276 --> 01:28:39,278
I have to put that...

1541
01:28:39,528 --> 01:28:40,696
behind.

1542
01:28:45,200 --> 01:28:46,493
Funny how life goes.

1543
01:28:46,702 --> 01:28:48,579
It’s amazing. Amazing.

1544
01:29:15,147 --> 01:29:16,940
Let’s go. It’s late.

1545
01:29:17,191 --> 01:29:19,234
It’s definitely late.

1546
01:29:19,485 --> 01:29:21,445
Christmas Eve, and late.

1547
01:29:21,695 --> 01:29:22,613
Let’s go.

1548
01:29:24,823 --> 01:29:27,284
Everyone says ‘I love you...’

1549
01:29:27,409 --> 01:29:30,454
the cop on the corner
and the burglar too.

1550
01:29:30,662 --> 01:29:32,998
Christmas Eve in Paris.

1551
01:29:33,165 --> 01:29:34,458
What a year!

1552
01:29:34,875 --> 01:29:37,878
And that sort of brings us
to the end of our story.

1553
01:29:38,170 --> 01:29:40,756
I told Skylar someone should
write it up as a movie.

1554
01:29:41,048 --> 01:29:44,968
She said ‘Better be a musical,
or no one will believe it.’

1555
01:29:45,177 --> 01:29:46,053
By the way...

1556
01:29:46,303 --> 01:29:49,348
that night
I met a terrific guy.

1557
01:29:49,556 --> 01:29:51,934
I mean, talk about sexy!

